  "prompt": "Can I deposit cash without cheque in SBI?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deposit cash in your State Bank of India (SBI) account without a cheque. There are several methods to do this:\n\n1. **Cash Deposit Machine (CDM):** SBI has cash deposit machines that allow you to deposit cash directly into your account. You need to follow the on-screen instructions, enter your account details, and insert the cash into the machine.\n\n2. **Over-the-Counter Deposit:** You can visit an SBI branch and fill out a cash deposit slip. Hand the slip along with the cash to the bank teller, who will process the deposit for you.\n\n3. **Mobile Banking:** In some cases, you might be able to transfer cash using a mobile banking app if you are holding cash with a cash withdrawal from another account.\n\n4. **Internet Banking:** If your account is linked with other services, you can transfer funds from one SBI account to another or use other banking services.\n\nAlways ensure you keep the transaction receipt provided after any cash deposit as proof of the deposit.",
